                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in the main hand.
The note mentions šum ʾAgame Gäbrä Ḫәywät as the commissioner and ʾAśratä Maryam as the scribe. Besides, his wife Maḫḍäntä Maryam, his father Nәblä Dәngәl, his mother ʾArsema, and his children Wäldä Giyorgis, Wäldä Mikaʾel, qes Wäldä ʾArägawi, qes Zärʾa Yoḥannәs, Zä-Śәllase, Wäldä Yoḥannәs, Täklä Yoḥannәs, Wälättä Mikaʾel are mentioned.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Stamp of the church, poorly visible: fol. 5r.&#xD;
- The scribe used small script for antiphons on fols. 41ra-42rb; 64rb-65va; 71ra-va; 73rb-74vb; 80vb-81vb; 83va; 85vb-84rb; 90ra-rb; 95va-vb.&#xD;
- Two or three chains of black and red dots as text dividers: fols. 13v, 24r, 135ra, 161va, 186ra.&#xD;
- The word ʾәgäle is marked by thin lines above and below: e.g., fols. 34ra, 35ra, 57rb, 84ra.&#xD;
- Corrections written interlineally: e.g., fols. 7vb, 19va, 21vb, 22rb, 29ra.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: e.g., 54va, 68vb, 75va, 150ra, 168rb.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by thin lines above and below words: fols. 16va, 151ra, 176ra.&#xD;
- A small cross in the inter column of fol. 142r next to the word matäb.</item>
